article.headline: Monmouth, N.J. 69, Wagner 58
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Dejan Delic had a game-high 15 points and four assists as Monmouth beat Wagner 69-58 on Thursday night. Whitney Coleman added 13 point and Marques Alston finished with 10 for Monmouth (6-8, 1-1 in Northeast Conference), which hit 55 percent of its shots and won its fourth straight game. Justin Drummond scored 14 points to lead the Seahawks (4-9, 1-1), while Joey Mundweiler and James Ulrich each had 11 points. Ulrich also had a game-high nine rebounds, but Wagner had a poor night from the floor, hitting just 35 percent of its shots. The teams traded baskets early on, but Monmouth took command with a 21-7 run early in the second half and held double-digit leads for the rest of the game.
